# Cursor Rules for HPC Cluster Project

## Project Context
This is an enterprise-grade HPC (High Performance Computing) cluster infrastructure project, 100% open-source, designed for SUSE 15 SP4 deployment.

## Code Standards

### Shell Scripts
- Always use `#!/bin/bash` with `set -euo pipefail`
- Use 2-space indentation
- Variable names in UPPER_CASE
- Add comments for complex sections
- Validate user inputs

### Documentation
- Markdown with consistent formatting
- Table of contents for long documents
- Working code examples
- Links to official documentation

### Docker
- Multi-stage builds when possible
- Minimal images (Alpine if possible)
- Appropriate labels
- Healthchecks

## Architecture
- 2 frontend nodes (HA)
- 6 compute nodes
- Full monitoring stack (Prometheus, Grafana, InfluxDB, Loki)
- Enterprise authentication (LDAP/Kerberos, FreeIPA)
- 27+ scientific applications
- Big Data & ML support

## Important Notes
- All passwords must be changed in production
- Security is critical - follow SECURITY.md
- Documentation is extensive (93 guides)
- Support for air-gapped deployment
